---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'How tool.news handles your data, what cookies we use, and how to opt out.';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-10';
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 lg:px-6 lg:py-16" style="color: var(--color-text);">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-lg space-y-8 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <p>
          tool.news is a free, open catalog of developer tools published by HeyLabs. We try to collect the
          minimum amount of data needed to keep the site online and improve it. This page tells you exactly
          what is collected, by whom, and how to turn it off.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">1. What we collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare network logs.</strong> Our hosting provider (Cloudflare) automatically logs
            requests for security and abuse protection: IP address, user-agent, request path, response status.
            These logs are retained by Cloudflare and not under our direct control. We do not store them
            ourselves.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics.</strong> Anonymous, cookie-free pageview counts and Core Web
            Vitals from real visits, used to understand traffic and page performance. No personal identifiers
            are collected.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft Clarity (only if you accept cookies).</strong> Anonymous session replays and
            click heatmaps so we can see how people use the catalog and fix usability problems. Clarity
            assigns a random ID and stores it in a cookie. We never see your name, email, or precise
            location, and we mask all input field contents by default.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">2. What we do NOT collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          <li>We have no user accounts, so we don&rsquo;t collect names, emails, or passwords.</li>
          <li>We have no advertising network. We don&rsquo;t track you across other sites.</li>
          <li>We do not sell, rent, or share personal information with third parties for advertising.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">3. Cookies we use</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          On first visit you&rsquo;ll see a banner asking whether to allow analytics cookies. If you decline,
          no cookies are set and Microsoft Clarity does not load. If you accept, the following cookies are set
          by Clarity:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          <li><code>_clck</code> — anonymous user ID, kept 1 year</li>
          <li><code>_clsk</code> — session ID, kept 1 day</li>
          <li>A handful of related session-management cookies, all set by clarity.ms</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          We also use <code>localStorage</code> to remember your cookie choice so we don&rsquo;t pester you on
          every visit. That entry is purely client-side and never leaves your browser.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">4. Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          If you&rsquo;re in the EU, EEA, or UK, you have the right to access, correct, or delete personal
          data we hold about you, to object to processing, and to lodge a complaint with your local data
          protection authority. Because we don&rsquo;t hold accounts, the most useful right here is to
          withdraw consent for Microsoft Clarity at any time using the &ldquo;Your Privacy Choices&rdquo;
          link in the footer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">5. Your rights (California, CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected, to request
          deletion, and to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information. We do not sell your data,
          and we do not share it for cross-context behavioral advertising. To opt out of Microsoft Clarity
          tracking entirely, click <strong>Your Privacy Choices</strong> in the footer and choose
          &ldquo;Decline.&rdquo;
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">6. Data retention</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Cloudflare Web Analytics retains aggregated data for up to 6 months under our free plan. Microsoft
          Clarity retains anonymous session data for up to 13 months per Microsoft&rsquo;s
          <a
            href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/clarity/setup-and-installation/data"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="underline underline-offset-2"
            style="color: var(--color-text);"
          >data policy</a>.
          We do not export or join this data with any other system we run.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">7. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          We&rsquo;ll update this page when our data practices change. The &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date at
          the top reflects the most recent change.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">8. Contact</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Questions or requests: visit
          <a
            href="https://heylabs.co"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="underline underline-offset-2"
            style="color: var(--color-text);"
          >heylabs.co</a>
          for contact details.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
